The paper discusses the application of machine learning and optimization techniques for ride sharing prediction, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implications of ride sharing in smart cities, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of optimization techniques such as Network Lasso and ADMM also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
